<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="molecular diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Molecular diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
We sequenced the holotype for COI, and its sequence is closest to an undescribed species from Malaysia (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B." order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">B.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spMalaysia11 in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1101/2020.11.23.394510" author="Doorenweerd, C" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" refId="B7" refString="Doorenweerd, C, Jose, MS, Leblanc, L, Barr, N, Geib, S, Chung, AYC, Dupuis, J, Ekayanti, A, Fiegalan, ER, Hemachandra, KS, Chia-lung, MAH, 2020. DNA barcodes and reliable molecular identifications in a diverse group of invasive pests: lessons from Bactrocera fruit flies on variation across the COI gene, introgression, and standardization. bioRxiv. https://doi.org/10.1101/2020.11.23.394510" title="DNA barcodes and reliable molecular identifications in a diverse group of invasive pests: lessons from Bactrocera fruit flies on variation across the COI gene, introgression, and standardization. bioRxiv." url="https://doi.org/10.1101/2020.11.23.394510" year="2020">Doorenweerd et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
) at 11.19% pairwise distance. The 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. quasienochra" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quasienochra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">B. quasienochra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sequence has an even greater distance to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. enochra" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enochra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">B. enochra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[N = 6].
</paragraph>
