<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
The species name is a noun in apposition, derived from the Latin adverb 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">quasi</emphasis>
(just as if) used in conjunction with the epithet of the species it closely resembles; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. enochra" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enochra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">B. enochra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
